After watching this movie ,I was shocked from one simple fact of how easily a good idea for a movie is destroyed.

This movie almost had it all: some good realistic characters (like George Simmons and Ira Wright) ,good cast acting (especiely and surprisingly from Seth Rogen and Adam Sandler) ,good and surprising end- but the movie's lenght is simply too long and endless ,not mentioning that there a lot of unnecessary scenes and it's just not working...usually , movies are less then two hours.

The whole sequence of events was good during the first 30 minutes but then it was just got really boring and more pointless with some unnecessary details until the end of it. 

In conclusion: big disappointment ,could be much better.
